pull/3419.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>Currently we don't pass <code>-g -G</code> flags to nvcc when <code>DEBUG=1</code>.  This makes using <code>cuda-gdb</code> to debug device code particularly difficult. This PR enables such flags when <code>CUDA_DEBUG=1</code>.</p>\n<p>Tested with script in <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"268832322\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/3309\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/pytorch/pytorch/issues/3309/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/3309\">#3309</a>. Verified that <code>cuda-gdb</code> can break in and display device code successfully.</p>", "body_text": "Currently we don't pass -g -G flags to nvcc when DEBUG=1.  This makes using cuda-gdb to debug device code particularly difficult. This PR enables such flags when CUDA_DEBUG=1.\nTested with script in #3309. Verified that cuda-gdb can break in and display device code successfully.", "body": "Currently we don't pass `-g -G` flags to nvcc when `DEBUG=1`.  This makes using `cuda-gdb` to debug device code particularly difficult. This PR enables such flags when `CUDA_DEBUG=1`.\r\n\r\nTested with script in https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/3309. Verified that `cuda-gdb` can break in and display device code successfully."}